                                                                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="12951055" author="davsclaus" created="Tue, 3 Mar 2009 10:49:14 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Send mail to dev forum for discussion first.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12951078" author="davsclaus" created="Tue, 3 Mar 2009 13:17:21 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This is also related to let ResolverUtil be pluggable so you can let it work in other platforms such as JBoss, WebSphere.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Will add stuff for both strategies to be pluggable.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12951044" author="njiang" created="Tue, 3 Mar 2009 13:59:58 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Since some ResolverUtil created without any  camel context involved,  we need to find more specify way to do this.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12951047" author="davsclaus" created="Tue, 3 Mar 2009 14:24:11 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;ResolverUtil is used in&lt;br/&gt;
camel-spring&lt;br/&gt;
camel-osgi&lt;br/&gt;
camel-bindy&lt;br/&gt;
camel-core&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I got the stuff on camel-core working. I know I can get bindy working as well as it can get hold of the camel context when doing marhsall/unmarshal.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;camel-spring and camel-osgi should be possible. camel-spring is creating the camel-context.&lt;br/&gt;
And camel-osgi should set its osgi aware resolvers instead of the default one when it creates the camel context.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;So I do think its doable.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12950996" author="njiang" created="Tue, 3 Mar 2009 14:39:59 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;So we need to add a method in camel context to get a right ResolverUtil now.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12951023" author="davsclaus" created="Tue, 3 Mar 2009 14:45:23 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Yes I am adding a new SPI interface for the pluggable resolvers. And having getters/setters on the CamelContext so you can plugin which one you want to use.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;And let camel-spring auto discover them in the spring bean registry if any provided so it can be automatic set just by declaring a bean in spring XML&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12951018" author="davsclaus" created="Tue, 3 Mar 2009 16:58:55 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I have committed it to trunk. There is now a getClassResolver() on CamelContext that works as ObjectHelper does.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;But it allows us to provide another class resolver for OSGi if needed. &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12951022" author="cmoulliard" created="Wed, 4 Mar 2009 08:31:42 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Do I have to change something in Camel-bindy code or the modification will be transparent not matter if deployment is done on osgi server or not ?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12951021" author="hadrian" created="Wed, 4 Mar 2009 15:25:29 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;@Charles, yes, there should be no difference if the deployment is in an osgi container or not.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12951008" author="cmoulliard" created="Wed, 4 Mar 2009 15:29:38 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I made a test and everything works fine. Thanks &lt;img class=&quot;emoticon&quot; src=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/images/icons/emoticons/wink.png&quot; height=&quot;16&quot; width=&quot;16&quot; align=&quot;absmiddle&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; border=&quot;0&quot;/&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12949680" author="davsclaus" created="Fri, 31 Jul 2009 06:34:11 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Closing 2.0m1 tickets&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
